abstract_ssm: This scrapbook contains clippings related the Moscow Trials in Russia between 1936 and 1936. Compiled by labor organizer and sociologist and Abraham Nash, this scrapbook contains assorted clipping from publications on the political left as well as mainstream periodicals. Clippings in the scrapbook also relate to Trotsky's exile from Russia and tensions between supporters of Trotsky and Soviet leaders during this period.
corpname_ssm: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives
